<class module="videoDriver" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.videoDriver.alarm.BIVideoAlarmRecorder" name="BIVideoAlarmRecorder" packageName="com.tridium.videoDriver.alarm" public="true" interface="true" abstract="true" category="interface">
<description>
Video Driver Components that wish to take special action when a Niagara&#xa; AX alarm occurs should implement this class.&#xa; &#xa; Here is how this class plugs in the overall grand scheme of things:&#xa; 1.) An integrator adds a BVideoAlarmRecipient to the station under the&#xa; alarm service.&#xa; 2.) The integrator links the BVideoAlarmRecipient to the appropriate&#xa; alarm class(es).&#xa; 3.) On the property sheet of the BVideoAlarmRecipient, the integrator&#xa;  chooses a component in the station to serve as the &#x27;video responder&#x27;.&#xa; 4.) The component in the station that he or she chooses will be a&#xa; component from a video driver.&#xa; 5.) The component from a video driver will also implement this interface.&#xa; 6.) The component&#x27;s &#x27;handleAlarm(BAlarmRecord) method will be called whenever&#xa; the BVideoAlarmRecipient receives an alarm from the alarm service.&#xa; 7.) The particular video driver component that implements this interface will&#xa; take special action, such as to ask a video camera to start recording.
</description>
<tag name="@see">BVideoAlarmRecipient</tag>
<tag name="@author">lperkins</tag>
<implements>
<type class="javax.baja.sys.BInterface"/>
</implements>
<!-- com.tridium.videoDriver.alarm.BIVideoAlarmRecorder.startRecordingAlarm(javax.baja.alarm.BAlarmRecord) -->
<method name="startRecordingAlarm"  public="true" abstract="true">
<description>
Defines a method that will be called on the station-side VM to&#xa; process an alarm record. This method will be called by BVideoAlarmRecipient.&#xa; &#xa; A video driver should use this callback to ask a camera to start&#xa; recording as a result of some alarm condition that has occurred within&#xa; the Niagara AX framework but outside of the camera system&#x27;s realm.
</description>
<parameter name="alarmRecord">
<type class="javax.baja.alarm.BAlarmRecord"/>
<description>
- This is the alarm record from the Niagara AX alarm&#xa; service.
</description>
</parameter>
<return>
<type class="void"/>
</return>
</method>

